modules.description: Provides functions for measuring execution time, counting function calls, and aggregating performance metrics. Operates on timestamps, counters, and event logs generated during program execution. Used to identify bottlenecks in real-time systems and optimize critical code paths.

Processes OCaml ASTs to analyze and modify function parameters, extracting counts and generating parameterized expressions. Operates on parse trees, location data, and filename strings to transform and inspect function definitions. Used to instrument code for profiling by dynamically creating parameter lists and mapping files to module names.

Tracks and reports execution time of specific code blocks, using a hash table to store profiled data and ref cells to track durations and counts. Provides functions to profile code with exclusivity checks, generate diagnostic strings, and print GC statistics. Enables detailed timing analysis for performance debugging in real-time applications.
